Scan and connect to a Laird BLE device running a Heart rate monitor smartBASIC app. Once connected the sensor data and position will be displayed and plotted on the graph.

Click the icon on the top right to connect to multiple BLE heart rate devices
Scan and connect to multiple Laird BLE HR devices.

Scan and connect to a Laird BLE device running a Proximity smartBASIC app. Once connected the you can change the Link loss and Immmediate alert characteristics.

The Serial (VSP) functionality allows text data to be sent from an Android device to a Laird BLE module that is in VSP mode and back again. This application can be used to remotely control the device through the use of AT commands.

Program Laird BLE modules remotely with this new Over the Air (OTA) application. Remove the cables by wirelessly programming the Laird BLE module, Bluetooth Low Energy module with the new smartBASIC programming language.

Note: The module needs to be in VSP command mode to work.

The Batch functionality enables you to send scripts wirelessly over the air to the Laird BLE module. These scripts can be custom-made and use AT commands to control the module remotely.

Note: The module needs to be in VSP command mode to work.
The SPP functionality allows text data to be sent using BT Classic from an Android device to a Laird BT900 module that is in SPP mode and back again.
